(Military Asset Management System) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Description) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This solution provides an initial full-stack framework for managing military assets such as) Tj
T*
(vehicles, weapons and ammunition across multiple bases. The platform supports asset purchases,) Tj
T*
(transfers, assignments to personnel, and expenditure logging while surfacing opening balances,) Tj
T*
(closing balances and net movements through a secure dashboard.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Primary Objectives) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* Improve transparency across bases) Tj
T*
(* Streamline logistics workflows) Tj
T*
(* Preserve traceability for all operational transactions) Tj
T*
(* Enforce accountability through role-based access control) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Assumptions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* The requested technology constraint was prioritized: backend uses Node.js + Express,) Tj
T*
(database uses MongoDB, and frontend uses React + Vite) Tj
T*
(* Balances are derived from transaction history rather than a separate inventory snapshot) Tj
T*
(engine) Tj
T*
(* Closing balance is treated as: Opening Balance + Purchases + Transfer In - Transfer Out -) Tj
T*
(Assigned - Expended) Tj
T*
(* Base Commander and Logistics Officer accounts are linked to a single assigned base) Tj
T*
(* Transfers are treated as completed movements for the initial framework) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Limitations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* No attachment storage for transfer or procurement documents in this first version) Tj
T*
(* No approval workflow for transfers or assignments yet) Tj
T*
(* No pagination or advanced analytics layer yet) Tj
T*
(* MongoDB was used because it was explicitly requested, even though the original prompt also) Tj
T*
(mentioned choosing a relational database) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Tech Stack & Architecture) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Frontend) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* React 18 with Vite) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
