() Tj
T*
(How Logging Is Handled) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* Morgan logs incoming HTTP requests at the API layer) Tj
T*
(* A dedicated `AuditLog` collection stores business transaction events) Tj
T*
(* Every create operation for purchases, transfers, assignments and expenditures writes an) Tj
T*
(audit entry) Tj
T*
(* Each audit log stores:) Tj
T*
(- actor) Tj
T*
(- action type) Tj
T*
(- module) Tj
T*
(- resource id) Tj
T*
(- metadata such as base, equipment type and quantity) Tj
T*
(- IP address) Tj
T*
(- user agent) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Benefits) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* Supports operational traceability) Tj
T*
(* Enables audit readiness and accountability reviews) Tj
T*
(* Simplifies incident investigation and change tracking) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Setup Instructions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Prerequisites) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* Node.js 20+ recommended) Tj
T*
(* npm 10+) Tj
T*
(* MongoDB local instance or MongoDB Atlas) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Backend Setup) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Open the `backend` folder) Tj
T*
(2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`) Tj
T*
(3. Configure:) Tj
T*
(- `PORT`) Tj
T*
(- `MONGODB_URI`) Tj
T*
(- `JWT_SECRET`) Tj
T*
(- `CLIENT_URL`) Tj
T*
(4. Run `npm install`) Tj
T*
(5. Run `npm run seed`) Tj
T*
(6. Run `npm run dev`) Tj
ET
endstream
